Origin, Meaning, And History Of Keegan,

Keegan originated from an anglicized and shortened version of Mac Aodhag√°in. Mac Aodhag√°in means a son or descendant of Aodhag√°n, a double diminutive of the Irish personal name Aodh. Aodh is derived from an Old Irish word √Åed, which means ‚Äòfiery, flaming or ardent.‚Äô The name Keegan implies ‚Äòson of Aodh or son of fire.‚Äô Aodh is the name of the Celtic God of the fiery underworld.

Keegan is also a surname derived from the anglicization of the Irish Gaelic clan named Mac Aodhag√°in. The people of this clan provided hereditary legal to the Burkes of Clanricarde and the Conchobhair Kings of Connacht.

Hundreds of years ago, the Keegan family in Ireland went by the Gaelic name Mac Aodhagain, typically Anglicized as Hugh. The family asserts that they are descended from Saint and Bishop Eoghan, ‚Äòof Ardsratha, now Ardstraw, in the county of Tyrone and the diocese of Derry. He was related to the Leinster chieftains since he descended from Ugaine Mor on his father‚Äôs side, and he claimed kinship with the Ulster families via his mother, Muindech.

In Celtic origin, the name means ‚ÄòSon of Egan.‚Äô In Gaelic, the name refers to ‚ÄòSmall and fiery.‚Äô In American and Irish origins, the name means ‚ÄòA thinker, fiery, or a Form of Hugh.‚Äô

According to a different account, the name is derived from ‚Äòthe cineal Eoghain. They were the ‚Äògenus‚Äô or progeny of Eoghan, a famous Irish chief contemporary with St. Patrick. Owen and Eugene are the anglicized versions of the moniker.

The surname Keegan was first found in the 13th century in County Tipperary in South-central Ireland, where they held the family seat from ancient times.

KEE-gahn is the common pronunciation of the name. There are several other spellings for Egan, Eagan, MacEgan, Kegan, and Kegan are the few spelling variations of the name. Keegie, Kee, and Key are some cute nicknames for the name.

The fictional world has seen the appearance of the name a few times. For example, a fictional character named Keegan Butcher-Baker appears in the BBC soap opera EastEnders. He is Tiffany Butcher Baker‚Äôs husband.

Keegan‚Äôs Zodiac Sign As Per Western Astrology

Western astrology includes the construction of a horoscope based on the person‚Äôs exact time of birth and location to understand the positions of the planet, stars, and zodiac signs at that time. However, in popular culture, it is often narrowed down to the sun sign, which depends on the person‚Äôs birth date.There are 12 zodiac signs, each having dominant traits, planetary rulers, elemental connection, and more.

Zodiac sign or Sun sign

The Earth‚Äôs orbit around the sun is divided into 12 zodiac signs covering 30-degree sectors. According to Western astrology, the zodiac or sun sign depends on the sun‚Äôs position in one of these sectors at the time of your birth. Starting from the sun‚Äôs position at the March equinox, the chart goes anti-clockwise from Aries, followed by Taurus, Gemini, Cancer, Leo, Virgo, Libra, Scorpio, Sagittarius, Capricorn, Aquarius, and Pisces. These signs are ruled by planetary bodies - Mars, Venus, Mercury, Moon, Sun, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune. Furthermore, they are categorized into triplicities or elemental signs - fire, water, air, and earth - that govern their characteristics. Each of these zodiac signs features certain personality traits that may determine how a person presents themselves.

Each zodiac sign in Western astrology is linked to a specific range of dates in the year. Unlike Vedic astrology, where names can sometimes be used to infer astrological details, Western astrology relies entirely on the birth date.
